Ukrainian steelmaker OJSC Dneprovsky
Metallurgical Plant, a part of Industrial Union of Donbass,
plans to start upgrading its rolled-metal unit next month,
 Ekonomicheskie Izvestia  newspaper reported, without citing
anyone.  The upgrade, which will cost 1.5 billion hryvnia ($187
million), will make possible an increase in rolled-metal
production to 1.95 million tons a year, from 700,000 tons at
present, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kateryna Choursina in Kiev at 
 kchoursina@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
